########################
# History of the AVsub #
########################

AVsub 1.1.1 [2021.05.12]
------------------------
- F1110: Fixed an error that could cause the temporary subtitle file not to be deleted when exiting.
- C1110: If specified, the FFmpeg command is now also shown for automatic operations as well.
- Code improvements.


AVsub 1.1.0 [2021.05.03]
------------------------
- F1100: Fixed the error "TypeError: startfile() takes no keyword arguments" in Python 3.5.
- N1100: Added a command-line option that can change audio channels.
- N1101: Added a command-line option that shows the FFmpeg command during processing.
- N1102: It is now checked if there is a new version for AVsub when no arguments are specified.
- C1100: Root folders are no longer considered hidden in Linux.
- C1101: Fatal FFmpeg error is now also displayed at the end of output for convenience.
- Code improvements.
- Exit messages have been made more meaningful.
- User interface has been improved.


AVsub 1.0.2 [2021.04.12]
------------------------
- F1020: Fixed an "AttributeError" that could occur on exiting.
- C1020: Unprocessed items in a folder can now be determined as "not processed" after an exit request.
- C1021: The default value for the subtitle font size has been changed from 18 to 20.
- C1022: All other temporary folders are now collected under one main temporary folder.
- C1023: Temporary folder now opens only in Windows operating system.
- Contradictory option check has been improved.
- Exit messages have been made more meaningful.
- User interface has been improved.


AVsub 1.0.1 [2021.03.16]
------------------------
- Code improvements.
- User interface has been improved.


AVsub 1.0.0 [2021.03.10]
------------------------
- First version.
